OL,3,CEmpty shops, poor transport and a drug
OL,4,Cproblem: What can be done for Redditch?
OL,6,F"So it's all about engaging these
OL,7,Fpeople every day. To try to steer them
OL,8,Fclear of committing crimes - and
OL,9,Fhopefully long term will reduce crime
OL,10,Fthemselves during that time."
OL,12,FBut he insisted it wasn't about
OL,13,F'decriminalising' their behaviour.
OL,15,F"These people shouldn't get away with
OL,16,Fwhat they're doing, which causes alarm
OL,17,Fand distress to members of the public,
OL,18,Fbusinesses and visitors to the town,"
OL,19,Fhe said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@]O]wD@AOUzD@eO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/13
