OL,3,CEmpty shops, poor transport and a drug
OL,4,Cproblem: What can be done for Redditch?
OL,6,F"These people have been using drugs
OL,7,Fand alcohol for decades, and we aren't
OL,8,Fgoing to solve that overnight. But we
OL,9,Fare willing to put the effort in."
OL,11,FBut of course, the police can't solve
OL,12,Feverything. And on top of crime, the
OL,13,Fother issues people mentioned to us
OL,14,Fwere things like transport, provision
OL,15,Ffor people with disabilities, and
OL,16,Fempty shops.
OL,18,FThose are the kinds of questions the
OL,19,Flocal council has to answer.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@bO]
